SIMPLE: plummet
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Plummet
<hw>Plum"met</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>plommet</ets>, OF. <ets>plommet</ets>, fr. <ets>plom</ets>,
<ets>plum</ets>, lead, F. <ets>plomb</ets>. See <er>Plumb</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A piece of lead attached to a line, used in sounding
the depth of water.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I'll sink him deeper than e'er <qex>plummet</qex> sounded.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A plumb bob or a plumb line. See under
<er>Plumb</er>, <pos>n.</pos></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Hence, any weight.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>A piece of lead formerly used by school children to
rule paper for writing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Plummet line</b></col>, <cd>a line with a plummet; a
sounding line.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Plumming</ent>⟦br⟧
